The paper discusses the societal impact of big data and proposes a research roadmap for Europe to optimize its use. This topic falls under the category of Computer Science and Society (cs.CY) as it deals with the social and ethical implications of big data. The paper also covers topics related to data management, processing, analytics, protection, and visualization, which are all relevant to the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the legal and political aspects of big data, which could be classified under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the need for standardization, which is relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of delivering social impact and skills development, which could be classified under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
